// =============================================================================
//  STRATEGY:    LongScalper_FixedLimitEntry_Pro v1.0
//  AUTHOR:      Drafted with help from Claude
//  RELATIONSHIP TO LongScalper v2.6:
//      - This is a SEPARATE strategy. It does NOT modify LongScalper v2.6.
//      - It reuses v2.6's proven trading logic patterns (entry, brackets,
//        trailing stop, orphan check, audit log) but with one key difference:
//        v2.6 fires automatically on enable (one-shot auto-fire).
//        THIS strategy fires only when the FIRE button is clicked
//        (or in the future, when an external signal source calls FireOrder()).
//
//  WHY A NEW STRATEGY:
//      - User wants a manual / signal-driven launcher with a visible control panel.
//      - Today: human sees a J9 signal -> clicks FIRE -> one bracketed trade runs.
//      - Future: external API/file feed calls FireOrder() -> same execution path.
//      - The button is a manual stand-in for the future signal feed.
//
//  HOW IT WORKS:
//      1. Add this strategy to a chart (NQ recommended), enable it.
//      2. A WPF control panel pops out.
//      3. Set parameters in the standard NT properties dialog (qty, target,
//         stops, multipliers, FixedLimitPrice if using FixedPrice mode).
//      4. Click FIRE LONG to place ONE bracketed buy.
//      5. Strategy manages the trade to exit (target / stop / trailing / manual).
//      6. After exit, strategy disables itself - same one-shot model as v2.6.
//      7. To trade again, re-enable the strategy.
//
//  THREADING NOTES (THIS IS WHERE THE FILE-1 ATTEMPT FAILED):
//      - WPF window is created on the UI dispatcher, NOT the strategy thread.
//      - All panel updates from strategy thread go through Dispatcher.BeginInvoke.
//      - Button clicks (UI thread) set volatile flags read by OnBarUpdate.
//        Order placement happens on the strategy thread, never from button handlers.
//      - Window is closed in State.Terminated via Dispatcher.Invoke, reference nulled.
//      - Window's Closing event tracked so a user-X'd panel doesn't leave a dead ref.
//
// =============================================================================

